# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  PROOF — Choti wall kyun move karein? (Why always move shorter?)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  Maan lo  height[left] < height[right]  hai
#  Suppose  height[left] < height[right]
#
#  Agar hum left ko fix rakhein aur right ko move karein:
#  If we keep left fixed and move right inward:
#
#    → width   ZAROOR kam hogi  (right andar aa gaya)
#       width   DEFINITELY decreases (right moved inward)
#
#    → height  MAXIMUM height[left] hi rahegi  (choti side = ceiling)
#       height  is still CAPPED at height[left] (shorter side = ceiling)
#
#    → area    ZAROOR kam ya barabar hogi — kabhi zyada nahi
#       area   can NEVER increase — only decrease or stay same
#
#  Isliye left ko move karna hi sensible hai
#  Therefore moving left is the only logical choice
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  COMMON GALTIYAN (Common Mistakes)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  GALAT 1 — Badi wall move karna
#  WRONG 1 — Moving the taller wall
#
#      if height[left] > height[right]:
#          left += 1          ← GALAT! Badi wall move ki, choti nahi
#                               WRONG! Moved the taller wall
#
#  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  GALAT 2 — Max height use karna, min nahi
#  WRONG 2 — Using max height instead of min
#
#      area = max(height[left], height[right]) * width   ← GALAT!
#      area = min(height[left], height[right]) * width   ← SAHI!
#
#  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  GALAT 3 — Loop condition mein <= use karna
#  WRONG 3 — Using <= in loop condition
#
#      while left <= right:   ← GALAT! Jab left==right ek hi element hai
#                               WRONG! When left==right it's same element
#      while left < right:    ← SAHI! Pair chahiye, ek element nahi
#                               RIGHT!  We need a pair, not one element
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
